Other notable winners include:
- Geraldine McCaughrean for children's fiction, her third Not the End of the World award, and a growing influence in the wider audience due to this recognition;
- Susan Fletcher's Eve Green for first novel, marking her as an emerging author to watch;
- John Guy's The Life of Mary Queen of Scots in biography, described as impressive and moving scholarship;
- Michael Symmons Roberts for poetry, blending mysticism, erotica, and philosophy;
- Geraldine McCaughrean again for children's fiction, following previous wins in 1987 and 1994.
